long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1280156 journalctl log
Description of problem: SELinux prevents from start radicale.service with: $ sudo systemctl start radicale.service
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): radicale-1.1.2-1.fc26.noarch
How reproducible: Install Fedora Server DVD x86_64 and install radicale.
Steps to Reproduce: 1. Install Fedora Server DVD x86_64 2. Upgrade: $ sudo dnf upgrade 3. Install radicale: $ sudo dnf install radicale 4. Start service: $ sudo systemctl start radicale
Actual results: Job for radicale.service failed because the control process exited with error code. See "systemctl status radicale.service" and "journalctl -xe" for details.
Expected results: radicale.service starts.
Additional info: radicale.service worked on Fedora 25.
Removing PrivateDevices=true from the service unit file fixes the issue. I will submit an update soon.
